COMMON COUNCIL PROCEEDINGS.; Board of Aldermen

docs.lead_paragraph: President COMPTON in the Chair. Petitions were received from Wm. H. Delano and others, to be organized as a Hose Company in the Eighth Ward. Of Joseph H. Godwin and others for a sewer in Elizabeth-street. A communication was received from Mr. Isaac, Edwards, Collector of Assessments, nominating Julius Johnson as Deputy Collector, in place of Robert McGary. Nomination confirmed.

headline.main: LATER FROM HAVANA.; ARRIVAL OF THE STEAMER GEORGE LAW. POLITICAL ARRESTS IN CUBA. Bull Fights--The Ballet and other Amusements. General and Miscellaneous News

docs.lead_paragraph: The Mail steamer George Law, Capt. JOHN McGOWAN, arrived at this port on Saturday morning. She left New-Orleans Sept. 30, for New York, via Havana, at which port she arrived early on the morning of the 3d inst., and having embarked the mails and passengers, sailed at noon of the same day for this port.
